#conclusion aria-hidden="true"
  markdown:
    - Headings are the most common way to navigate within web pages
    - Headings are announced with their level
    - Skipping heading levels is bad style (#{link_to 'HTML5 heading outlines', 'https://developer.mozilla.org/de/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Sections_and_Outlines_of_an_HTML5_document'} are not yet supported by NVDA)
    - When browsing using `↓` or `↑`, the element's meta data is read **before** the element's content (<q>Heading level 1. Programming languages.</q>)
    - When targetting headings directly using `h` or `1` to `6`, the element's meta data is read **after** the element's content (<q>Programming languages. Heading level 1.</q>)

